@Deleted User I´ve seen some messages behind. I thought there are some translation credits in yuzu. Never the less how does the review of translation process works? How could someone review a language they dont speak?
Deleted User 6/5/2019 4:18 PM
For now, there aren't any credits for translations besides in Transifex itself. You can request a new language, or join a existing one. Translators, well, translate, and reviewers review the translations and suggest changes. For the language to be imported into Yuzu, the minimal requirements are approximately 50% translated and 50% reviewed, and that's why I always recommend to grab reviews, since translator work alone won't get into the emulator.
4:19 PM
Translators and reviewers should be doing work on their native language.

Stars
what does "Unfuse FMA" means ?
Mary 4/19/2021 10:04 PM
FMA stands for fused multiply-add. It's a CPU instruction that does a multiple and add as a single fused instruction. "unfuse" means to split it up into two separate instructions: multiply, then add. See also: https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fused_multiply-add
Stars
also what is the context for "Setting CPU to Debug Mode" ? is that on option or a message box ?
Mary 4/19/2021 10:05 PM
the CPU accuracy combobox has a Debug Mode option

docteh 8/31/2022 2:54 PM
@flTobi Please fix the Danish translation for "Deadzone: %1%", the translation is missing leading % symbol, so a user sees Dødzone: 1% regardless of what it deadzone actually is.
Fs00 9/12/2022 7:36 AM
Hello everyone! I've found out an issue regarding a particular translatable string in Yuzu: "Remove Installed Game %1?". Since I wasn't able to understand what the placeholder was for, I dug into the code and discovered that the %1 can get replaced with Contents, Update or DLC (https://github.com/yuzu-emu/yuzu/blob/master/src/yuzu/main.cpp#L1999-L2016). The problem is that the code is assuming that the part leading to the placeholder ("Remove Installed Game") won't change regardless of the placeholder, which is not the case in other languages such as Italian. In the latter language for example, I need to add an article before Contents, Update or DLC which is not the same in all cases. So, instead of using a placeholder, I'd recommend having 3 different translatable strings for the 3 scenarios ("Remove Installed Game Contents?", "Remove Installed Game Update?", "Remove Installed Game DLC?") in order to leave more room to translators. Thank you!

4:26 PM

leolawliet
I want to know how to contribute to the android project, if you are using a special framework/pipeline to get this tested on the phones and if you have some automation suites to run
SleepingSnake 7/4/2023 4:27 PM
We use GitHub for hosting the project and its development. The main yuzu repo is the same one that the Android builds are compiled from. As for a special framework for testing, no. It's hard to standardise testing with Android devices when there are a crap-ton of different hardware, drivers, and operating system differences between all supported devices. Generally speaking, we have our testers (role in the server) test out changes that are likely to cause regressions, and the Devs themselves usually have both a compatible Mali and Adreno device to test their changes with.
SleepingSnake
We use GitHub for hosting the project and its development. The main yuzu repo is the same one that the Android builds are compiled from. As for a special framework for testing, no. It's hard to standardise testing with Android devices when there are a crap-ton of different hardware, drivers, and operating system differences between all supported devices. Generally speaking, we have our testers (role in the server) test out changes that are likely to cause regressions, and the Devs themselves usually have both a compatible Mali and Adreno device to test their changes with.
leolawliet 7/4/2023 4:28 PM
That's cool, so let me ask you, the main yuzu in github is public but the compiling for early access and not early access are different, they just came from that public repo
4:29 PM
(early access has the latest commit and build and the other one is older)
SleepingSnake 7/4/2023 4:29 PM
Mainline is directly compiled from the public repo. EA isn't, due to the nature of it being a paid app (similar to desktop).
leolawliet 7/4/2023 4:30 PM
I see, so I would be contributing to the not paid app, in case i'm developing a "paid feature", would that cause any issues?
4:30 PM
(like the existing open issues in github that users requests but you are already developing)
4:31 PM
(in ea)
SleepingSnake 7/4/2023 4:31 PM
I think you may be misunderstanding the monetization model. EA only contains features for testing that will get merged into master (mainline), once it has been tested to be stable.
4:32 PM
EA is essentially paid QA testing and a way to support developers.
4:32 PM
As such, there are no specific paid features that are for EA only.
4:33 PM
So, if you open up a pull request for a feature, code will first get reviewed. Then the EA tag will get applied to the PR on GitHub, which then triggers the change to land in the next EA build.
4:34 PM
After that's been tested there, it gets merged into mainline.
4:34 PM
So you develop off of master, and the changes get tested in EA before they get merged.
4:34 PM
(unless the change is very small)
leolawliet 7/4/2023 4:38 PM
So the workflow would be something like this?
4:39 PM
SleepingSnake
(unless the change is very small)
leolawliet 7/4/2023 5:06 PM
sorry for the quick picture, i did it in 5' on draw.io
5:06 PM
it's to understand better the release process
SleepingSnake 7/4/2023 5:17 PM
There is no private GitHub branch for public contributions. We just use GitHub CI to build the a master build with the PR applied and test that.
Narr the Reg 7/4/2023 5:56 PM
@leolawliet We have two builds. mainline == master + mainline tagged PR and EA == master + mainline + EA tagged PR. We don't add code that is not public. All contributors submit a pull request, after the initial review is done we decide if it needs testing or merging directly. If it needs testing we add the corresponding tag. Mainline https://github.com/yuzu-emu/yuzu/pulls?q=is%3Apr+is%3Aopen+label%3Amainline-merge EA https://github.com/yuzu-emu/yuzu/pulls?q=is%3Apr+is%3Aopen+label%3Aearly-access-merge
5:57 PM
A new mainline releases every day. While EA is triggered once each time a PR that is merged.
Narr the Reg
A new mainline releases every day. While EA is triggered once each time a PR that is merged.
